Univarient Analysis

library(data.table)

Myproject3 <- fread("C:/Users/kumarm29/Documents/DS/DATA Sets/Project/dataset_00_with_header.csv")
 
# variable  x051

# Summary of the Data

summary(Myproject3$x051)
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
##  0.0000  0.0000  0.0000  0.1101  0.0000  7.0000
#Total number of values excluding NA

NROW(Myproject3$x051) - NROW(Myproject3[which(is.na(Myproject3$x051)),])
## [1] 100000
#Now visualize the statistics

#Histogram

hist(Myproject3$x051,
     main = "Histogram of x051",
     xlab = "x051")
abline(v =mean(Myproject3$x051, na.rm = TRUE),col = "royalblue",
 lwd = 2)

#Boxplot
boxplot(Myproject3$x051,
        main = toupper("Boxplot of x051"),
        ylab = "x051",
        col = "blue")

#Density Plot
d <- density(Myproject3$x051, na.rm = TRUE)
plot(d, main = "Kernel density of x051")
polygon(d, col = "red", border = "blue")
abline(v =mean(Myproject3$x051, na.rm = TRUE),col = "royalblue",
 lwd = 2)

NROW(Myproject3$x097) - NROW(Myproject3[which(is.na(Myproject3$x097)),])
## [1] 100000
#Now visualize the statistics
#Histogram
hist(Myproject3$x097,
     main = "Histogram of x097",
     xlab = "x097")
abline(v =mean(Myproject3$x097, na.rm = TRUE),col = "royalblue",
 lwd = 2)

#Boxplot
boxplot(Myproject3$x097,
        main = toupper("Boxplot of x097"),
        ylab = "x097",
        col = "blue")

#Density Plot
d <- density(Myproject3$x097, na.rm = TRUE)
plot(d, main = "Kernel density of x097")
polygon(d, col = "red", border = "blue")
abline(v =mean(Myproject3$x097, na.rm = TRUE),col = "royalblue",
 lwd = 2)
